{
  "texts": [
    "(iii) ([Moc99, Definition 15.4 (i)]) A field k is said to be sub-p-adic if there exists a prime number p and a finitely generated field extension L of the p-adic number field Q p such that k is isomorphic to a subfield of L.",
    "Recall also that the Grothendieck conjecture has been proved for hyperbolic curves over sub-p-adic fields [Moc99] and, later, in [Moc15], [Hos17] etc., Mochizuki and Hoshi try to extend such results to hyperbolic curves over Kummer-faithful fields.",
    "Thus it would be interesting to supply many examples of Kummer-faithful fields that are not sub-p-adic.",
    "It is known that:",
    "• if a Galois extension k of a Kummer-faithful field of characteristic zero is highly Kummer-faithful, then k is Kummer-faithful [OT22, Proposition 2.8]; • a sub-p-adic field is Kummer-faithful, but the converse is not true [Moc15, Remark 1.5.4, (i) and (iii)]."
  ]
}